			    STPJS 345</div>
  <p class="cont">I have the truth of God,<span class="footRef">1</span> and show that ninety-nine out of every hundred professing religious
  ministers are false teachers,<span class="footRef">2</span> having no authority,<span class="footRef">3</span> while they pretend to hold the keys of God&rsquo;s
  kingdom<span class="footRef">4</span> on earth, and was to kill them because they are false teachers,<span class="footRef">5</span> it would deluge the whole
  world with blood.</p>
  <p class="std">I will prove that the world is wrong, by showing what God is. I am going to enquire after God;<span class="footRef">6</span>
  for I want you all to know him, and to be familiar with him;<span class="footRef">7</span> and if I am bringing you to a
  knowledge of him,<span class="footRef">8</span> all persecutions against me ought to cease. You will then know that I am his
  servant;<span class="footRef">9</span> for I speak as one having authority.<span class="footRef">10</span></p>
  <div class="topic">God an Exalted Man</div>
  <p class="std">I will go back to the beginning before the world was,<span class="footRef">11</span> to show what kind of being God is. What
  sort of a being was God in the beginning? Open your ears and hear,<span class="footRef">12</span> all ye ends of the earth,<span class="footRef">13</span> for
  I am going to prove it to you by the Bible, and to tell you the designs of God<span class="footRef">14</span> in relation to the
  human race, and why He interferes with the affairs of man.</p>
  <p class="std"><i>God himself was once as we are now, and is an exalted man, and sits enthroned in yonder</i>
  <i>heavens!  That is the great secret. If the veil were rent</i><span class="footRef">15</span> <i>today, and the great God who holds this</i>
  <i>world in its orbit, and who upholds all worlds</i><span class="footRef">16</span> <i>and all things by his power, was to make himself</i>
  <i>visible,&mdash;I say, if you were to see him today, you would see him like a man in form</i><span class="footRef">17</span><i>&mdash;like yourselves</i>
  <i>in all the person, image, and very form as a man;</i><span class="footRef">18</span> <i>for Adam was created in the very fashion, image</i>
  <i>and likeness of God,</i><span class="footRef">19</span> <i>and received instruction from, and walked, talked and conversed with him,</i><span class="footRef">20</span>
  <i>as one man talks and communes with another.</i><span class="footRef">21</span></p>
  <p class="std">In order to understand the subject of the dead, for consolation of those who mourn for the loss
  of their friends, it is necessary we should understand the character and being of God and how he
  came to be so; for I am going to tell you how God came to be God. We have imagined and supposed
  that God was God from all eternity.<span class="footRef">22</span> I will refute that idea, and take away the veil, so that you may
  see.</p>
  <p class="std">These are incomprehensible ideas to some, but they are simple. <i>It is the first principle of the</i>
  <i>Gospel to know for a certainty the Character of God, and to know that we may converse with him</i>
  <i>as one man converses with another,</i><span class="footRef">23</span> <i>and that</i></p>
